name: Mostafa Othman
headline: Robotics Software Engineer
creator: False
bio:
As an emerging Robotics Software Engineer, I've honed my skills through various internships and competitive experiences. I had the privilege to work at Rapyuta Robotics in Tokyo, where I was actively involved in diagnosing and rectifying issues during robot deployment, streamlining deployment workflows, and enhancing product, process, and operations.

Throughout my journey, I have cultivated a unique skill set in managing complex systems, with a focus on orchestrating bilateral communication for the teleoperation of robotics manipulators. My academic pursuits have delved deep into the intersection of Robotics and computer vision, providing me with profound insights into Robot Reinforcement Learning, Developmental Robotics, and Deep Generative Models.

Challenges have played a vital role in my learning and growth, serving as practical platforms for applying my skills. One notable challenging project was the 'Tele-operation and Control of Kuka iiwa Robotic Arm using Haptic Device and Force Feedback for Resilience Assembly of Peg-in-Hole Task', where I explored various fields and platforms, ranging from computer vision to fully autonomous systems.

I am well-versed in utilizing a range of technical platforms, including Unity3D, MATLAB, SOLIDWORKS, Arduino, ROS, Python, C++, C#, Git, Docker, and TensorFlow. These tools have empowered me to tackle complex challenges and develop innovative solutions.

In addition to my technical expertise, I strongly believe in the power of effective leadership and teamwork. During my tenure as the Chairman of the Robotronics student club at my university, I mentored teams for various competitions and gained valuable management experience while overseeing numerous projects.

As I continue to navigate this exciting career path, I am driven to apply my passion and skills to cutting-edge robotics and software development projects. I am committed to expanding my knowledge and proficiency in this rapidly evolving field, contributing to the advancement of robotics technology and creating a positive impact in the lives of individuals and communities.

headline: Senior Product Manager
creator: False
bio:
Product Manager with over 9 years of experience in the oil and gas sector. Successfully developed and implemented geology-focused products and spearheaded the creation of a digital technology management system comprising 11 applications, utilized by corporate users and partners. Proven track record in identifying customer needs and delivering tailored solutions through strategic product vision and execution. 


ACHIEVEMENTS
• Successfully managed 20+ digital projects, including 2 government-level products: the personal account for subsoil users and digital reporting solutions
• Achieved 16 intellectual property (IP) outcomes, comprising 9 programs and algorithms and 7 databases
• Authored 13 publications and received recognition for the Best Innovative Idea in the Ministry of Energy
• Directed multi-management of 4 cross-functional teams, each with up to 10 members,ensuring collaboration and successful project delivery
• Developed and conducted 6 training programs, empowering over 550 employees to effectively apply acquired skills in their roles


SKILLS
• Experience working with key methodologies and software: Agile, Project Methodology, CustDev, Design Thinking, JTBD, OKR, KPI, CJM, UX/UI principles, Figma, Jira, Confluence, Trello, Power BI, Qlik Sense
• Oversee all stages of the product lifecycle, including design, development, and implementation
• Demonstrate strategic thinking by crafting compelling product visions and actionable strategies
• Managing a multidisciplinary team, interaction with stakeholders, users, and teams
• Design and deliver engaging training sessions and seminars
• Proactive and strategic self-development management
• Languages: English: B2, Serbian: A1, Russian: native speaker

name: Parth Kalkar
headline: AI Product & Solutions Architect | LLM & AI Agent Expert | Data Science & ML Leader | Empowering AI-Driven Innovation & Industry Leadership
creator: True
bio:
Experienced AI engineer and product manager with a proven track record in AI engineering, data science, and project management. Adept at applying AI to solve complex tech innovation challenges.

Professional Experience:
- 3 years in AI engineering and management
- 6 years in data science and programming
- Led cross-functional teams (max 20), delivering projects punctually and economically

Key Achievements:
1. Pioneered an AI-driven R&D tax credit analysis platform, revolutionizing the consultancy process for SME companies. This innovative system increased identified qualifying activities by 35%, resulting in an average of $5M in additional tax credits annually and a 87% approval rate from authorities.

2. Engineered a cutting-edge neural stock trading system leveraging deep learning and real-time market data analysis. This AI-powered platform achieved a 32% increase in annual returns for institutional investors, outperformed standard market indices by 28%, and reduced trading risks by 40% through advanced predictive modelling and adaptive strategy optimization.

3. Architected and launched "TOM," an AI-powered code analysis and improvement tool, revolutionizing software development practices. This innovative platform uses advanced machine learning algorithms to detect and suggest fixes for code smells, security vulnerabilities, and style inconsistencies in real time. TOM reduced bug rates by 45%, improved code quality scores by 60%, and increased developer productivity by 25% across 10,000+ users from leading tech companies worldwide.

Skills: 
1. Strategic Product Development:
   • Vision, strategy, roadmapping
   • Agile/Scrum, Lean Startup, MVP
   • User-centric design, prototyping
   • Product lifecycle & go-to-market

2. Data-Driven Decision Making:
   • A/B testing, KPIs, analytics
   • Financial modeling, pricing
   • Market research, competitive analysis

3. Customer-Centric Research:
   • User research, VoC programs
   • Persona development, segmentation

4. AI/ML Engineering:
   • Frameworks: LangChain, Transformers, PyTorch
   • Techniques: NLP, Deep Learning, Reinforcement Learning
   • MLOps: Kubeflow, MLflow
   • Cloud AI platforms: AWS SageMaker, Vertex AI

5. Technical Proficiency:
   • Programming: Python, FastAPI
   • Cloud platforms: AWS (EC2, S3), Google Cloud (Compute Engine)
   • Version control: Git, GitHub, GitLab

Objective:
Seeking to leverage my unique blend of technical expertise and product vision to lead cutting-edge AI initiatives that revolutionize industries and create lasting value for users and stakeholders alike.

headline: Принимаю предложения
creator: False
bio:
Я имею 2-летний опыт в разработке pet-проектов, а также highload Minecraft серверов (коммерческих).
Обладаю опытом в написании, проектировании, оптимизации, отладке и поддержке приложений/сервисов.

Выбрал Java и Backend-разработку благодаря их ключевой роли в создании сложных, масштабируемых и надежных систем. Java как язык разработки привлекла меня своей универсальностью и обширной экосистемой.

С уважением отношусь как к своему, так и к чужому времени, поэтому стараюсь планировать и соблюдать сроки. За пару лет опыта научился строить долгосрочные благополучные отношения с командой и клиентами.

Люблю активный и силовой спорт. Занимаюсь в зале и серьезно отношусь к бегу.

Также владею английским языком на уровне C1.

Ссылка на мой гитхаб: https://github.com/ppxxd

name: Ilnar Shafigullin (Ph.D.)
headline: Data scientist
creator: False
bio:
For over a decade, I've been teaching at university level and leading impactful projects in the EdTech industry. My passion lies at the intersection of education and technology, especially the fields of Data Science and Artificial Intelligence, with a particular focus on Computer Vision.

During my tenure at GeekBrains, a pioneering EdTech company, I masterminded a transformative educational program - the "Developer" project. This initiative replaced more than 80% of the company's existing offerings, bringing an innovative approach to online education. Its effects have rippled across the online education market in Russia and neighboring countries, setting a new standard and inspiring many other organizations.

At present, the program proudly serves over 30,000 students, underscoring its success and wide acceptance.

Another highlight of my career was at Ak Bars Digital Technologies, where I implemented a machine learning project centered around real-time passenger tracking in public transportation. The project spanned from model selection and dataset acquisition to equipment installation and operation, utilizing technologies such as Jetson Nano.

Moreover, I'm actively engaged in product development leveraging generative networks, particularly the LLM (Large Language Model).

I hold a Ph.D. in Physics and Mathematics, and have an extensive collection of scientific publications listed on https://www.mathnet.ru/eng/person68614. My teaching portfolio comprises Mathematical Analysis, Optimization Methods, Algorithms and Data Structures, and Computer Science (Java).

In addition to my technical prowess, I've proven my leadership skills in managing large teams (25-30 people) in the EdTech and franchising sectors.

Beyond the professional realm, I am a Candidate Master of Sports in chess and have spent five years teaching the Brazilian zouk social dance.

My analytical mindset is balanced by effective communication skills and a congenial demeanor. My passion for innovation, coupled with my team orientation, has consistently enabled me to drive and contribute to breakthrough solutions.

name: Matias Correa Hudson
headline: Ingeniero Civil Mecánico | Liderazgo en Operaciones Industriales | Simulación de Ingeniería | Mantenimiento Estratégico | Innovación en Robótica e IA | Optimización de Procesos | Gestión de Proyectos Corporativos
creator: False
bio:
Perfil Profesional

Ingeniero Civil Mecánico con experiencia en liderazgo y gestión de mantenimiento industrial en empresas de alto nivel. Especializado en optimizar procesos, reducir costos operativos y garantizar la continuidad operacional mediante soluciones innovadoras y técnicas avanzadas.  

Experiencia Profesional

- Supervisor de Mantenimiento Industrial - Arcor
Lidero equipos multidisciplinarios en la implementación de planes de mantenimiento preventivo y correctivo, logrando mejoras productivas y reducción de tiempos de inactividad en plantas industriales.  

- Jefe de Mantenimiento - Sociedad Industrial Kunstmann S.A.
Gestioné tres plantas industriales, optimizando procesos de mantenimiento y liderando proyectos clave. Logré reducir en un 800% las paradas de planta por fallas mediante mejoras en sistemas y procesos.  

- Jefe de Proyecto - Quiborax S.A.
Coordiné proyectos industriales, gestionando equipos técnicos y asegurando la excelencia operativa en cada etapa, desde la planificación hasta la ejecución.  

Habilidades Destacadas
- Diseño y simulación avanzada de sistemas mecánicos.  
- Gestión de proyectos industriales y optimización de procesos.  
- Implementación de metodologías ágiles: Scrum, Kanban y Lean Management.  
- Reducción de costos y mejora de la eficiencia operativa.  

Certificaciones y Formación 
- Diplomado en Planificación, Control y Gestión - Universidad de Chile.
